40Mt 11:21 "How terrible it will be for you, Chorazin! How terrible for you too, Bethsaida! If the miracles which were performed in you had been performed in Tyre and Sidon, the people there would have long ago put on sackcloth and sprinkled ashes on themselves, to show that they had turned from their sins! 
40Mt 11:22 I assure you that on the Judgment Day God will show more mercy to the people of Tyre and Sidon than to you! 
40Mt 11:23 And as for you, Capernaum! Did you want to lift yourself up to heaven? You will be thrown down to hell! If the miracles which were performed in you had been performed in Sodom, it would still be in existence today! 
40Mt 11:24 You can be sure that on the Judgment Day God will show more mercy to Sodom than to you!" 
40Mt 11:25 At that time Jesus said, "Father, Lord of heaven and earth! I thank you because you have shown to the unlearned what you have hidden from the wise and learned. 
40Mt 11:26 Yes, Father, this was how you were pleased to have it happen. 
40Mt 11:27 "My Father has given me all things. No one knows the Son except the Father, and no one knows the Father except the Son and those to whom the Son chooses to reveal him. 
40Mt 11:28 "Come to me, all of you who are tired from carrying heavy loads, and I will give you rest. 
40Mt 11:29 Take my yoke and put it on you, and learn from me, because I am gentle and humble in spirit; and you will find rest. 
40Mt 11:30 For the yoke I will give you is easy, and the load I will put on you is light." 
40Mt 12:1 Not long afterward Jesus was walking through some wheat fields on a Sabbath. His disciples were hungry, so they began to pick heads of wheat and eat the grain. 
40Mt 12:2 When the Pharisees saw this, they said to Jesus, "Look, it is against our Law for your disciples to do this on the Sabbath!" 
40Mt 12:3 Jesus answered, "Have you never read what David did that time when he and his men were hungry? 
40Mt 12:4 He went into the house of God, and he and his men ate the bread offered to God, even though it was against the Law for them to eat it - -only the priests were allowed to eat that bread. 
40Mt 12:5 Or have you not read in the Law of Moses that every Sabbath the priests in the Temple actually break the Sabbath law, yet they are not guilty? 
40Mt 12:6 I tell you that there is something here greater than the Temple. 
40Mt 12:7 The scripture says, 'It is kindness that I want, not animal sacrifices.' If you really knew what this means, you would not condemn people who are not guilty; 
40Mt 12:8 for the Son of Man is Lord of the Sabbath." 
40Mt 12:9 Jesus left that place and went to a synagogue, 
40Mt 12:10 where there was a man who had a paralyzed hand. Some people were there who wanted to accuse Jesus of doing wrong, so they asked him, "Is it against our Law to heal on the Sabbath?" 
40Mt 12:11 Jesus answered, "What if one of you has a sheep and it falls into a deep hole on the Sabbath? Will you not take hold of it and lift it out? 
40Mt 12:12 And a human being is worth much more than a sheep! So then, our Law does allow us to help someone on the Sabbath." 
40Mt 12:13 Then he said to the man with the paralyzed hand, "Stretch out your hand." He stretched it out, and it became well again, just like the other one. 
40Mt 12:14 Then the Pharisees left and made plans to kill Jesus. 
40Mt 12:15 When Jesus heard about the plot against him, he went away from that place; and large crowds followed him. He healed all the sick 
40Mt 12:16 and gave them orders not to tell others about him. 
40Mt 12:17 He did this so as to make come true what God had said through the prophet Isaiah�� 
40Mt 12:18 "Here is my servant, whom I have chosen, the one I love, and with whom I am pleased. I will send my Spirit upon him, and he will announce my judgment to the nations. 
40Mt 12:19 He will not argue or shout, or make loud speeches in the streets. 
40Mt 12:20 He will not break off a bent reed, nor put out a flickering lamp. He will persist until he causes justice to triumph, 
40Mt 12:21 and on him all peoples will put their hope." 
40Mt 12:22 Then some people brought to Jesus a man who was blind and could not talk because he had a demon. Jesus healed the man, so that he was able to talk and see. 
40Mt 12:23 The crowds were all amazed at what Jesus had done. "Could he be the Son of David?" they asked. 
40Mt 12:24 When the Pharisees heard this, they replied, "He drives out demons only because their ruler Beelzebul gives him power to do so." 
40Mt 12:25 Jesus knew what they were thinking, and so he said to them, "Any country that divides itself into groups which fight each other will not last very long. And any town or family that divides itself into groups which fight each other will fall apart. 
40Mt 12:26 So if one group is fighting another in Satan's kingdom, this means that it is already divided into groups and will soon fall apart! 
40Mt 12:27 You say that I drive out demons because Beelzebul gives me the power to do so. Well, then, who gives your followers the power to drive them out? What your own followers do proves that you are wrong! 
40Mt 12:28 No, it is not Beelzebul, but God's Spirit, who gives me the power to drive out demons, which proves that the Kingdom of God has already come upon you. 
40Mt 12:29 "No one can break into a strong man's house and take away his belongings unless he first ties up the strong man; then he can plunder his house. 
40Mt 12:30 "Anyone who is not for me is really against me; anyone who does not help me gather is really scattering. 
40Mt 12:31 For this reason I tell you�� people can be forgiven any sin and any evil thing they say; but whoever says evil things against the Holy Spirit will not be forgiven. 
40Mt 12:32 Anyone who says something against the Son of Man can be forgiven; but whoever says something against the Holy Spirit will not be forgiven - -now or ever. 
40Mt 12:33 "To have good fruit you must have a healthy tree; if you have a poor tree, you will have bad fruit. A tree is known by the kind of fruit it bears. 
40Mt 12:34 You snakes - -how can you say good things when you are evil? For the mouth speaks what the heart is full of. 
40Mt 12:35 A good person brings good things out of a treasure of good things; a bad person brings bad things out of a treasure of bad things. 
40Mt 12:36 "You can be sure that on the Judgment Day you will have to give account of every useless word you have ever spoken. 
40Mt 12:37 Your words will be used to judge you - -to declare you either innocent or guilty." 
40Mt 12:38 Then some teachers of the Law and some Pharisees spoke up. "Teacher," they said, "we want to see you perform a miracle." 
40Mt 12:39 "How evil and godless are the people of this day!" Jesus exclaimed. "You ask me for a miracle? No! The only miracle you will be given is the miracle of the prophet Jonah. 
