40Mt 25:41 "Then he will say to those on his left, 'Away from me, you that are under God's curse! Away to the eternal fire which has been prepared for the Devil and his angels! 
40Mt 25:42 I was hungry but you would not feed me, thirsty but you would not give me a drink; 
40Mt 25:43 I was a stranger but you would not welcome me in your homes, naked but you would not clothe me; I was sick and in prison but you would not take care of me.' 
40Mt 25:44 Then they will answer him, 'When, Lord, did we ever see you hungry or thirsty or a stranger or naked or sick or in prison, and we would not help you?' 
40Mt 25:45 The King will reply, 'I tell you, whenever you refused to help one of these least important ones, you refused to help me.' 
40Mt 25:46 These, then, will be sent off to eternal punishment, but the righteous will go to eternal life." 
40Mt 26:1 When Jesus had finished teaching all these things, he said to his disciples, 
40Mt 26:2 "In two days, as you know, it will be the Passover Festival, and the Son of Man will be handed over to be crucified." 
40Mt 26:3 Then the chief priests and the elders met together in the palace of Caiaphas, the High Priest, 
40Mt 26:4 and made plans to arrest Jesus secretly and put him to death. 
40Mt 26:5 "We must not do it during the festival," they said, "or the people will riot." 
40Mt 26:6 Jesus was in Bethany at the house of Simon, a man who had suffered from a dreaded skin disease. 
40Mt 26:7 While Jesus was eating, a woman came to him with an alabaster jar filled with an expensive perfume, which she poured on his head. 
40Mt 26:8 The disciples saw this and became angry. "Why all this waste?" they asked. 
40Mt 26:9 "This perfume could have been sold for a large amount and the money given to the poor!" 
40Mt 26:10 Jesus knew what they were saying, and so he said to them, "Why are you bothering this woman? It is a fine and beautiful thing that she has done for me. 
40Mt 26:11 You will always have poor people with you, but you will not always have me. 
40Mt 26:12 What she did was to pour this perfume on my body to get me ready for burial. 
40Mt 26:13 Now, I assure you that wherever this gospel is preached all over the world, what she has done will be told in memory of her." 
40Mt 26:14 Then one of the twelve disciples - -the one named Judas Iscariot - -went to the chief priests 
40Mt 26:15 and asked, "What will you give me if I betray Jesus to you?" They counted out thirty silver coins and gave them to him. 
40Mt 26:16 From then on Judas was looking for a good chance to hand Jesus over to them. 
40Mt 26:17 On the first day of the Festival of Unleavened Bread the disciples came to Jesus and asked him, "Where do you want us to get the Passover meal ready for you?" 
40Mt 26:18 "Go to a certain man in the city," he said to them, "and tell him�� 'The Teacher says, My hour has come; my disciples and I will celebrate the Passover at your house.' " 
40Mt 26:19 The disciples did as Jesus had told them and prepared the Passover meal. 
40Mt 26:20 When it was evening, Jesus and the twelve disciples sat down to eat. 
40Mt 26:21 During the meal Jesus said, "I tell you, one of you will betray me." 
40Mt 26:22 The disciples were very upset and began to ask him, one after the other, "Surely, Lord, you don't mean me?" 
40Mt 26:23 Jesus answered, "One who dips his bread in the dish with me will betray me. 
40Mt 26:24 The Son of Man will die as the Scriptures say he will, but how terrible for that man who will betray the Son of Man! It would have been better for that man if he had never been born!" 
40Mt 26:25 Judas, the traitor, spoke up. "Surely, Teacher, you don't mean me?" he asked. Jesus answered, "So you say." 
40Mt 26:26 While they were eating, Jesus took a piece of bread, gave a prayer of thanks, broke it, and gave it to his disciples. "Take and eat it," he said; "this is my body." 
40Mt 26:27 Then he took a cup, gave thanks to God, and gave it to them. "Drink it, all of you," he said; 
40Mt 26:28 "this is my blood, which seals God's covenant, my blood poured out for many for the forgiveness of sins. 
40Mt 26:29 I tell you, I will never again drink this wine until the day I drink the new wine with you in my Father's Kingdom." 
40Mt 26:30 Then they sang a hymn and went out to the Mount of Olives. 
40Mt 26:31 Then Jesus said to them, "This very night all of you will run away and leave me, for the scripture says, 'God will kill the shepherd, and the sheep of the flock will be scattered.' 
40Mt 26:32 But after I am raised to life, I will go to Galilee ahead of you." 
40Mt 26:33 Peter spoke up and said to Jesus, "I will never leave you, even though all the rest do!" 
40Mt 26:34 Jesus said to Peter, "I tell you that before the rooster crows tonight, you will say three times that you do not know me." 
40Mt 26:35 Peter answered, "I will never say that, even if I have to die with you!" And all the other disciples said the same thing. 
40Mt 26:36 Then Jesus went with his disciples to a place called Gethsemane, and he said to them, "Sit here while I go over there and pray." 
40Mt 26:37 He took with him Peter and the two sons of Zebedee. Grief and anguish came over him, 
40Mt 26:38 and he said to them, "The sorrow in my heart is so great that it almost crushes me. Stay here and keep watch with me." 
40Mt 26:39 He went a little farther on, threw himself face downward on the ground, and prayed, "My Father, if it is possible, take this cup of suffering from me! Yet not what I want, but what you want." 
40Mt 26:40 Then he returned to the three disciples and found them asleep; and he said to Peter, "How is it that you three were not able to keep watch with me for even one hour? 
40Mt 26:41 Keep watch and pray that you will not fall into temptation. The spirit is willing, but the flesh is weak." 
40Mt 26:42 Once more Jesus went away and prayed, "My Father, if this cup of suffering cannot be taken away unless I drink it, your will be done." 
40Mt 26:43 He returned once more and found the disciples asleep; they could not keep their eyes open. 
40Mt 26:44 Again Jesus left them, went away, and prayed the third time, saying the same words. 
40Mt 26:45 Then he returned to the disciples and said, "Are you still sleeping and resting? Look! The hour has come for the Son of Man to be handed over to the power of sinners. 
40Mt 26:46 Get up, let us go. Look, here is the man who is betraying me!" 
40Mt 26:47 Jesus was still speaking when Judas, one of the twelve disciples, arrived. With him was a large crowd armed with swords and clubs and sent by the chief priests and the elders. 
40Mt 26:48 The traitor had given the crowd a signal�� "The man I kiss is the one you want. Arrest him!" 
40Mt 26:49 Judas went straight to Jesus and said, "Peace be with you, Teacher," and kissed him. 
40Mt 26:50 Jesus answered, "Be quick about it, friend!" Then they came up, arrested Jesus, and held him tight. 
40Mt 26:51 One of those who were with Jesus drew his sword and struck at the High Priest's slave, cutting off his ear. 
40Mt 26:52 "Put your sword back in its place," Jesus said to him. "All who take the sword will die by the sword. 
40Mt 26:53 Don't you know that I could call on my Father for help, and at once he would send me more than twelve armies of angels? 
40Mt 26:54 But in that case, how could the Scriptures come true which say that this is what must happen?" 
40Mt 26:55 Then Jesus spoke to the crowd, "Did you have to come with swords and clubs to capture me, as though I were an outlaw? Every day I sat down and taught in the Temple, and you did not arrest me. 
40Mt 26:56 But all this has happened in order to make come true what the prophets wrote in the Scriptures." Then all the disciples left him and ran away. 
40Mt 26:57 Those who had arrested Jesus took him to the house of Caiaphas, the High Priest, where the teachers of the Law and the elders had gathered together. 
40Mt 26:58 Peter followed from a distance, as far as the courtyard of the High Priest's house. He went into the courtyard and sat down with the guards to see how it would all come out. 
40Mt 26:59 The chief priests and the whole Council tried to find some false evidence against Jesus to put him to death; 
40Mt 26:60 but they could not find any, even though many people came forward and told lies about him. Finally two men stepped up 
40Mt 26:61 and said, "This man said, 'I am able to tear down God's Temple and three days later build it back up.' " 
40Mt 26:62 The High Priest stood up and said to Jesus, "Have you no answer to give to this accusation against you?" 
40Mt 26:63 But Jesus kept quiet. Again the High Priest spoke to him, "In the name of the living God I now put you under oath�� tell us if you are the Messiah, the Son of God." 
40Mt 26:64 Jesus answered him, "So you say. But I tell all of you�� from this time on you will see the Son of Man sitting at the right side of the Almighty and coming on the clouds of heaven!" 
40Mt 26:65 At this the High Priest tore his clothes and said, "Blasphemy! We don't need any more witnesses! You have just heard his blasphemy! 
40Mt 26:66 What do you think?" They answered, "He is guilty and must die." 
40Mt 26:67 Then they spat in his face and beat him; and those who slapped him 
40Mt 26:68 said, "Prophesy for us, Messiah! Guess who hit you!" 
40Mt 26:69 Peter was sitting outside in the courtyard when one of the High Priest's servant women came to him and said, "You, too, were with Jesus of Galilee." 
40Mt 26:70 But he denied it in front of them all. "I don't know what you are talking about," he answered, 
40Mt 26:71 and went on out to the entrance of the courtyard. Another servant woman saw him and said to the men there, "He was with Jesus of Nazareth." 
40Mt 26:72 Again Peter denied it and answered, "I swear that I don't know that man!" 
40Mt 26:73 After a little while the men standing there came to Peter. "Of course you are one of them," they said. "After all, the way you speak gives you away!" 
40Mt 26:74 Then Peter said, "I swear that I am telling the truth! May God punish me if I am not! I do not know that man!" Just then a rooster crowed, 
40Mt 26:75 and Peter remembered what Jesus had told him�� "Before the rooster crows, you will say three times that you do not know me." He went out and wept bitterly. 
40Mt 27:1 Early in the morning all the chief priests and the elders made their plans against Jesus to put him to death. 
40Mt 27:2 They put him in chains, led him off, and handed him over to Pilate, the Roman governor. 
40Mt 27:3 When Judas, the traitor, learned that Jesus had been condemned, he repented and took back the thirty silver coins to the chief priests and the elders. 
40Mt 27:4 "I have sinned by betraying an innocent man to death!" he said. "What do we care about that?" they answered. "That is your business!" 
40Mt 27:5 Judas threw the coins down in the Temple and left; then he went off and hanged himself. 
40Mt 27:6 The chief priests picked up the coins and said, "This is blood money, and it is against our Law to put it in the Temple treasury." 
40Mt 27:7 After reaching an agreement about it, they used the money to buy Potter's Field, as a cemetery for foreigners. 
40Mt 27:8 That is why that field is called "Field of Blood" to this very day. 
40Mt 27:9 Then what the prophet Jeremiah had said came true�� "They took the thirty silver coins, the amount the people of Israel had agreed to pay for him, 
40Mt 27:10 and used the money to buy the potter's field, as the Lord had commanded me." 
40Mt 27:11 Jesus stood before the Roman governor, who questioned him. "Are you the king of the Jews?" he asked. "So you say," answered Jesus. 
40Mt 27:12 But he said nothing in response to the accusations of the chief priests and elders. 
40Mt 27:13 So Pilate said to him, "Don't you hear all these things they accuse you of ?" 
40Mt 27:14 But Jesus refused to answer a single word, with the result that the Governor was greatly surprised. 
40Mt 27:15 At every Passover Festival the Roman governor was in the habit of setting free any one prisoner the crowd asked for. 
40Mt 27:16 At that time there was a well-known prisoner named Jesus Barabbas. 
40Mt 27:17 So when the crowd gathered, Pilate asked them, "Which one do you want me to set free for you? Jesus Barabbas or Jesus called the Messiah?" 
40Mt 27:18 He knew very well that the Jewish authorities had handed Jesus over to him because they were jealous. 
40Mt 27:19 While Pilate was sitting in the judgment hall, his wife sent him a message�� "Have nothing to do with that innocent man, because in a dream last night I suffered much on account of him." 
40Mt 27:20 The chief priests and the elders persuaded the crowd to ask Pilate to set Barabbas free and have Jesus put to death. 
40Mt 27:21 But Pilate asked the crowd, "Which one of these two do you want me to set free for you?" "Barabbas!" they answered. 
40Mt 27:22 "What, then, shall I do with Jesus called the Messiah?" Pilate asked them. "Crucify him!" they all answered. 
40Mt 27:23 But Pilate asked, "What crime has he committed?" Then they started shouting at the top of their voices�� "Crucify him!" 
40Mt 27:24 When Pilate saw that it was no use to go on, but that a riot might break out, he took some water, washed his hands in front of the crowd, and said, "I am not responsible for the death of this man! This is your doing!" 
40Mt 27:25 The whole crowd answered, "Let the responsibility for his death fall on us and on our children!" 
40Mt 27:26 Then Pilate set Barabbas free for them; and after he had Jesus whipped, he handed him over to be crucified. 
40Mt 27:27 Then Pilate's soldiers took Jesus into the governor's palace, and the whole company gathered around him. 
40Mt 27:28 They stripped off his clothes and put a scarlet robe on him. 
40Mt 27:29 Then they made a crown out of thorny branches and placed it on his head, and put a stick in his right hand; then they knelt before him and made fun of him. "Long live the King of the Jews!" they said. 
40Mt 27:30 They spat on him, and took the stick and hit him over the head. 
40Mt 27:31 When they had finished making fun of him, they took the robe off and put his own clothes back on him. Then they led him out to crucify him. 
40Mt 27:32 As they were going out, they met a man from Cyrene named Simon, and the soldiers forced him to carry Jesus' cross. 
40Mt 27:33 They came to a place called Golgotha, which means, "The Place of the Skull." 
40Mt 27:34 There they offered Jesus wine mixed with a bitter substance; but after tasting it, he would not drink it. 
40Mt 27:35 They crucified him and then divided his clothes among them by throwing dice. 
40Mt 27:36 After that they sat there and watched him. 
40Mt 27:37 Above his head they put the written notice of the accusation against him�� "This is Jesus, the King of the Jews." 
40Mt 27:38 Then they crucified two bandits with Jesus, one on his right and the other on his left. 
40Mt 27:39 People passing by shook their heads and hurled insults at Jesus�� 
40Mt 27:40 "You were going to tear down the Temple and build it back up in three days! Save yourself if you are God's Son! Come on down from the cross!" 
40Mt 27:41 In the same way the chief priests and the teachers of the Law and the elders made fun of him�� 
40Mt 27:42 "He saved others, but he cannot save himself ! Isn't he the king of Israel? If he will come down off the cross now, we will believe in him! 
40Mt 27:43 He trusts in God and claims to be God's Son. Well, then, let us see if God wants to save him now!" 
40Mt 27:44 Even the bandits who had been crucified with him insulted him in the same way. 
40Mt 27:45 At noon the whole country was covered with darkness, which lasted for three hours. 
40Mt 27:46 At about three o'clock Jesus cried out with a loud shout, {\I "Eli, Eli, lema sabachthani?" which means, "My God, my God, why did you abandon me?"
40Mt 27:47 Some of the people standing there heard him and said, "He is calling for Elijah!" 
40Mt 27:48 One of them ran up at once, took a sponge, soaked it in cheap wine, put it on the end of a stick, and tried to make him drink it. 
40Mt 27:49 But the others said, "Wait, let us see if Elijah is coming to save him!" 
40Mt 27:50 Jesus again gave a loud cry and breathed his last. 
40Mt 27:51 Then the curtain hanging in the Temple was torn in two from top to bottom. The earth shook, the rocks split apart, 
40Mt 27:52 the graves broke open, and many of God's people who had died were raised to life. 
40Mt 27:53 They left the graves, and after Jesus rose from death, they went into the Holy City, where many people saw them. 
40Mt 27:54 When the army officer and the soldiers with him who were watching Jesus saw the earthquake and everything else that happened, they were terrified and said, "He really was the Son of God!" 
40Mt 27:55 There were many women there, looking on from a distance, who had followed Jesus from Galilee and helped him. 
40Mt 27:56 Among them were Mary Magdalene, Mary the mother of James and Joseph, and the wife of Zebedee. 
40Mt 27:57 When it was evening, a rich man from Arimathea arrived; his name was Joseph, and he also was a disciple of Jesus. 
40Mt 27:58 He went into the presence of Pilate and asked for the body of Jesus. Pilate gave orders for the body to be given to Joseph. 
40Mt 27:59 So Joseph took it, wrapped it in a new linen sheet, 
40Mt 27:60 and placed it in his own tomb, which he had just recently dug out of solid rock. Then he rolled a large stone across the entrance to the tomb and went away. 
40Mt 27:61 Mary Magdalene and the other Mary were sitting there, facing the tomb. 
40Mt 27:62 The next day, which was a Sabbath, the chief priests and the Pharisees met with Pilate 
40Mt 27:63 and said, "Sir, we remember that while that liar was still alive he said, 'I will be raised to life three days later.' 
40Mt 27:64 Give orders, then, for his tomb to be carefully guarded until the third day, so that his disciples will not be able to go and steal the body, and then tell the people that he was raised from death. This last lie would be even worse than the first one." 
40Mt 27:65 "Take a guard," Pilate told them; "go and make the tomb as secure as you can." 
40Mt 27:66 So they left and made the tomb secure by putting a seal on the stone and leaving the guard on watch. 
40Mt 28:1 After the Sabbath, as Sunday morning was dawning, Mary Magdalene and the other Mary went to look at the tomb. 
40Mt 28:2 Suddenly there was a violent earthquake; an angel of the Lord came down from heaven, rolled the stone away, and sat on it. 
40Mt 28:3 His appearance was like lightning, and his clothes were white as snow. 
40Mt 28:4 The guards were so afraid that they trembled and became like dead men. 
40Mt 28:5 The angel spoke to the women. "You must not be afraid," he said. "I know you are looking for Jesus, who was crucified. 
40Mt 28:6 He is not here; he has been raised, just as he said. Come here and see the place where he was lying. 
40Mt 28:7 Go quickly now, and tell his disciples, 'He has been raised from death, and now he is going to Galilee ahead of you; there you will see him!' Remember what I have told you." 
40Mt 28:8 So they left the tomb in a hurry, afraid and yet filled with joy, and ran to tell his disciples. 
40Mt 28:9 Suddenly Jesus met them and said, "Peace be with you." They came up to him, took hold of his feet, and worshiped him. 
40Mt 28:10 "Do not be afraid," Jesus said to them. "Go and tell my brothers to go to Galilee, and there they will see me." 
40Mt 28:11 While the women went on their way, some of the soldiers guarding the tomb went back to the city and told the chief priests everything that had happened. 
40Mt 28:12 The chief priests met with the elders and made their plan; they gave a large sum of money to the soldiers 
40Mt 28:13 and said, "You are to say that his disciples came during the night and stole his body while you were asleep. 
40Mt 28:14 And if the Governor should hear of this, we will convince him that you are innocent, and you will have nothing to worry about." 
40Mt 28:15 The guards took the money and did what they were told to do. And so that is the report spread around by the Jews to this very day. 
40Mt 28:16 The eleven disciples went to the hill in Galilee where Jesus had told them to go. 
40Mt 28:17 When they saw him, they worshiped him, even though some of them doubted. 
40Mt 28:18 Jesus drew near and said to them, "I have been given all authority in heaven and on earth. 
40Mt 28:19 Go, then, to all peoples everywhere and make them my disciples�� baptize them in the name of the Father, the Son, and the Holy Spirit, 
40Mt 28:20 and teach them to obey everything I have commanded you. And I will be with you always, to the end of the age." 
