41Mk 4:37 Suddenly a strong wind blew up, and the waves began to spill over into the boat, so that it was about to fill with water. 
41Mk 4:38 Jesus was in the back of the boat, sleeping with his head on a pillow. The disciples woke him up and said, "Teacher, don't you care that we are about to die?" 
41Mk 4:39 Jesus stood up and commanded the wind, "Be quiet!" and he said to the waves, "Be still!" The wind died down, and there was a great calm. 
41Mk 4:40 Then Jesus said to his disciples, "Why are you frightened? Do you still have no faith?" 
41Mk 4:41 But they were terribly afraid and began to say to one another, "Who is this man? Even the wind and the waves obey him!" 
