41Mk 15:29 People passing by shook their heads and hurled insults at Jesus�� "Aha! You were going to tear down the Temple and build it back up in three days! 
41Mk 15:30 Now come down from the cross and save yourself !" 
41Mk 15:31 In the same way the chief priests and the teachers of the Law made fun of Jesus, saying to one another, "He saved others, but he cannot save himself ! 
41Mk 15:32 Let us see the Messiah, the king of Israel, come down from the cross now, and we will believe in him!" And the two who were crucified with Jesus insulted him also. 
41Mk 15:33 At noon the whole country was covered with darkness, which lasted for three hours. 
41Mk 15:34 At three o'clock Jesus cried out with a loud shout, {\I "Eloi, Eloi, lema sabachthani?" which means, "My God, my God, why did you abandon me?"
41Mk 15:35 Some of the people there heard him and said, "Listen, he is calling for Elijah!" 
41Mk 15:36 One of them ran up with a sponge, soaked it in cheap wine, and put it on the end of a stick. Then he held it up to Jesus' lips and said, "Wait! Let us see if Elijah is coming to bring him down from the cross!" 
41Mk 15:37 With a loud cry Jesus died. 
41Mk 15:38 The curtain hanging in the Temple was torn in two, from top to bottom. 
41Mk 15:39 The army officer who was standing there in front of the cross saw how Jesus had died. "This man was really the Son of God!" he said. 
41Mk 15:40 Some women were there, looking on from a distance. Among them were Mary Magdalene, Mary the mother of the younger James and of Joseph, and Salome. 
